abstract: Mr. Biden, who had been delivering an animated version of his stump speech, was briefly knocked off course when someone needed medical attention.
snippet: Mr. Biden, who had been delivering an animated version of his stump speech, was briefly knocked off course when someone needed medical attention.
lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., who had been delivering an animated version of his stump speech, was briefly knocked off course when someone needed medical attention.
headline_main: Joe Biden gets back on track.

abstract: Fresh battle lines are being drawn that could lead to farm trade restrictions between the United States and Mexico, a letter from a top Mexican trade official seen by Reuters shows, despite the goodwill generated by the newly signed North American trade pact.
snippet: Fresh battle lines are being drawn that could lead to farm trade restrictions between the United States and Mexico, a letter from a top Mexican trade official seen by Reuters shows, despite the goodwill generated by the newly signed North American...
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Fresh battle lines are being drawn that could lead to farm trade restrictions between the United States and Mexico, a letter from a top Mexican trade official seen by Reuters shows, despite the goodwill generated by the newly signed North American trade pact.
headline_main: Exclusive: New Tensions Surface Over U.S.-Mexico Seasonal Farm Trade
headline_print_headline: Exclusive: New Tensions Surface Over U.S.-Mexico Seasonal Farm Trade

abstract: Hardline conservative Kris Kobach tried Saturday to reassure his fellow Kansas Republicans that if they nominate him for the U.S. Senate, they wouldn't have to worry that he'd lose to a Democrat again because no one is closer than he is to President Donald Trump in a state that Trump is expected to carry easily.
snippet: Hardline conservative Kris Kobach tried Saturday to reassure his fellow Kansas Republicans that if they nominate him for the U.S. Senate, they wouldn't have to worry that he'd lose to a Democrat again because no one is closer than he is to Preside...
lead_paragraph: OLATHE, Kan. — Hardline conservative Kris Kobach tried Saturday to reassure his fellow Kansas Republicans that if they nominate him for the U.S. Senate, they wouldn't have to worry that he'd lose to a Democrat again because no one is closer than he is to President Donald Trump in a state that Trump is expected to carry easily.
headline_main: Kansas Senate Rivals Try to Minimize Kobach's Ties to Trump
headline_print_headline: Kansas Senate Rivals Try to Minimize Kobach's Ties to Trump

abstract: Defense Secretary Mark Esper on Saturday approved a request from the Department of Health and Human Services for the possible use of military facilities to accommodate 1,000 people who may have to be quarantined upon arrival from overseas due to a new virus.
snippet: Defense Secretary Mark Esper on Saturday approved a request from the Department of Health and Human Services for the possible use of military facilities to accommodate 1,000 people who may have to be quarantined upon arrival from overseas due to a...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Defense Secretary Mark Esper on Saturday approved a request from the Department of Health and Human Services for the possible use of military facilities to accommodate 1,000 people who may have to be quarantined upon arrival from overseas due to a new virus.
headline_main: Pentagon Approves Using Military Bases to Quarantine 1,000
headline_print_headline: Pentagon Approves Using Military Bases to Quarantine 1,000

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump's task force on coronavirus will hold a public briefing on at 3:30 p.m. (2030 GMT), the White House said in a statement on Friday.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump's task force on coronavirus will hold a public briefing on at 3:30 p.m. (2030 GMT), the White House said in a statement on Friday.
headline_main: U.S. Coronavirus Task Force to Hold Briefing on Friday

abstract: In the final weekend before the Iowa caucuses, Bernie Sanders made his most forceful case yet that he was the most electable candidate.
snippet: In the final weekend before the Iowa caucuses, Bernie Sanders made his most forceful case yet that he was the most electable candidate.
lead_paragraph: INDIANOLA — On the final weekend before the Iowa caucuses, Bernie Sanders made his most forceful case yet that he was the most electable candidate, saying that he would defeat President Trump in the general election because he could excite voters, speak to the working class and expose Mr. Trump’s populist “hypocrisy.”

abstract: A flurry of newly released emails from scientists and top officials at the federal agency responsible for weather forecasting clearly illustrates the consternation and outright alarm caused by President Donald Trump’s false claim  that Hurricane Dorian could hit Alabama.
snippet: A flurry of newly released emails from scientists and top officials at the federal agency responsible for weather forecasting clearly illustrates the consternation and outright alarm caused by President Donald Trump’s false claim  that Hurricane D...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A flurry of newly released emails from scientists and top officials at the federal agency responsible for weather forecasting clearly illustrates the consternation and outright alarm caused by President Donald Trump’s false claim that Hurricane Dorian could hit Alabama.
headline_main: Emails Show the Fallout From Trump's Claims About Dorian
headline_print_headline: Emails Show the Fallout From Trump's Claims About Dorian

abstract: Inside the very weird homestretch in Iowa, where candidates were thin on the ground, but reporters were not.
snippet: Inside the very weird homestretch in Iowa, where candidates were thin on the ground, but reporters were not.
lead_paragraph: OTTUMWA, Iowa — As excellent as the Bernie Sanders event was — as excellent as it was to hear from the filmmaker Michael Moore and to eat Ben & Jerry’s ice cream scooped by the actual Ben and the actual Jerry, longtime Sanders supporters — it would have been even more excellent, was the general feeling, if Mr. Sanders himself had been able to come to Ottumwa.
